Newcastle Jets Team News

The Newcastle Jets FC were founded over twenty years ago and they have been a regular fixture in the Australian A-League for several seasons. This Aussie soccer team play their home games at McDonald Jones Stadium and this is one of the biggest A-League grounds with a capacity of 33,000. They claimed a victory in the 2008 Grand Final and we are on hand to provide the upcoming fixtures along with the latest lineups for each of their various domestic games taking place. Get the squad information and digest which players are most likely to compete in the next clash.

Next Newcastle Jets Fixtures

There are plenty of Newcastle Jets fixtures and they are announced at the beginning of the football season. It’s great to access the A-League fixtures, while you can also get the next fixtures when it comes to their participation in the FFA Cup. There are games that are played on a regular basis and it’s useful to know the date and time of every clash. This helps to plan ahead when it comes to placing pre-match and In-Play wagers on the soccer games involving the Jets.

Newcastle Jets Lineup Today

There are expected and predicted lineups for every Australian A-League clash. While the confirmed lineups aren’t known until much closer to kick-off, the predicted 11’s will help you understand the players who are most likely to be lining up in the next game. We look at the previous games involving this New South Wales team and digesting the lineups that were deployed in order to come up with our prediction. The Newcastle Jets lineups are always useful when being aware of which players are available.

The squad is packed with quality players, with some of them being new signings while others can remain with the football club for several seasons. We have lots of transfer news so that you can fathom the marquee signings that have been made during the transfer window, while you can also establish the outgoings although this Australian club will always aim to keep hold of their best players in order to compete well in the A-League each season.
